Title: Wplyw nauki na etyke zycia gospodarczego na podstawie sporu o ceny drapiezne/The Impact of Science on the Ethics of Economic Life under a Predatory Pricing Case
Abstract: Chicago School argues that the use of predatory strategy may not lead to a profit. Postchicago School, investigating this problem on
the basis of game theory, argues just the opposite. This dispute on the basis of theoretical economics, has an impact on ethics in economic
life. In a number of lawsuits companies rely on the views of the Chicago School to win, which raises the ethical concerns. 
Keywords: business ethics, predatory pricing, barriers to entry
